			<h2>Our Conduct</h2>
			<p>It is important for you to appreciate that TownSpot is not just a platform to showcase talent. It is a community of artist and viewers who appreciate artists. As with every flourishing community, it takes work to keep it that way. We are constantly working with users towards that end and ask that you help us.</p>
			<p>Accordingly, when TownSpot receives notification about misuse of Member Accounts, inappropriate Content, or inappropriate conduct or comments by users, we take these seriously. <span class="bold">Be aware that what TownSpot, in its sole discretion, deems are serious or repeated violations may lead to account termination. It does not matter if it's a first-time or repeated offense: We reserve this right and will exercise it if we deem it necessary</span>.</p>
			<p>Of course, if your Member Account is terminated, the consequences are serious: You will not be allowed to create a new Member Account, which means you will no longer be able to participate in our community as an artist, user or in any other manner associated with the benefits of a Member Account. </p>
			<p>Please take this to heart and take it seriously. Enjoy the amazing access to talent, growing audiences and new horizons that TownSpot offers you. Just use your common sense and observe our policies in doing so. Thanks! </p>
